@startuml observer-structure-abstract
' Observer, Behavioral. Abstract structure: canonical GoF roles only.
' Subject holds many Observers and notifies each on state change.
!include ../../pattern-preamble.iuml

interface Subject BEHAVIORAL_ROLE(Subject) {
  +attach(o : Observer)
  +detach(o : Observer)
  +notify()
}
class ConcreteSubject BEHAVIORAL_ROLE(ConcreteSubject) {
  -state
  +getState()
  +setState(s)
}
interface Observer BEHAVIORAL_ROLE(Observer) {
  +update()
}
class ConcreteObserver BEHAVIORAL_ROLE(ConcreteObserver) {
  +update()
}

Subject <|.. ConcreteSubject
Observer <|.. ConcreteObserver
Subject o-- "0..*" Observer : observers
ConcreteObserver --> ConcreteSubject : reads state

note as N
  Intent: notify a varying set of dependents when one object's state changes.
  Consequence: update order is unspecified; a notify can cascade into further updates.
end note
@enduml
